review_title: Tall Fescue Application
review_text: Per my research, it is recommended to not fertilize Fescue after March 15th. Reason being, Fescue is a cool season grass and as the weather warms, fertilizer will burn this type of grass. I know, the bag directions say it is good on all grass but you need to know your grass types recommendations as to when you apply any products to your yard. If you have Fescue it is best to apply fertilizer Oct-Nov or Feb-March.
review_lower: per my research, it is recommended to not fertilize fescue after march 15th. reason being, fescue is a cool season grass and as the weather warms, fertilizer will burn this type of grass. i know, the bag directions say it is good on all grass but you need to know your grass types recommendations as to when you apply any products to your yard. if you have fescue it is best to apply fertilizer oct-nov or feb-march.
